						<summary>

						<p>Slab buried into the bed of the stream.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalla [Sōmēśvara I] 1053-54 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is broken on all sides, hence, much of the information is lost. It seems to register a grant for a charitable Picoṭṭa by the queen (name lost) of king Trailōkyamalla. It mentions Bāguḻa paḻa. Probably Bāguḻa-paḻa was the ancient name of the present village Bāgalwāḍ.</p>						

						<p>In the date portion only Śaka 975 • • • • • 5, Thursday is available. It may correspond to 1053-54 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
